The package javascriptcore provides CMake targets:

    find_package(JavaScriptCore CONFIG REQUIRED)
    target_link_libraries(main PRIVATE
        JavaScriptCore::JavaScriptCore
        JavaScriptCore::WTF
        JavaScriptCore::bmalloc
        JavaScriptCore::jsc
        JavaScriptCore::icu-dt
        JavaScriptCore::icu-in
        JavaScriptCore::icu-uc
    )

Available targets:
  - JavaScriptCore::JavaScriptCore - Main JavaScriptCore engine
  - JavaScriptCore::WTF - WebKit Template Framework utilities
  - JavaScriptCore::bmalloc - bmalloc memory allocator
  - JavaScriptCore::jsc - JSC shell executable library
  - JavaScriptCore::icu-dt - ICU data library
  - JavaScriptCore::icu-in - ICU internationalization library
  - JavaScriptCore::icu-uc - ICU Unicode library

For basic usage, typically you only need:
    target_link_libraries(main PRIVATE JavaScriptCore::JavaScriptCore)
